@startuml
title IntentSpecification mandatory profile proposal

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #424242
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #424242

rectangle "TMF921 IntentSpecification\nbase resource model" as TMF #EEF2FF

rectangle "Intent management entity\nmandatory profile\n\nTMF-aligned, not TMF-minimal" as PROFILE #E8F5E9

TMF --> PROFILE : intent management entity conformance\ndefines minimum mandatory attributes

rectangle "Minimal DRAFT profile" as DRAFT #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "Create request minimum\n\n- name\n- version\n- @type\n- @baseType\n\nNot accepted on create:\n- lifecycleStatus\n\nOptional:\n- isBundle\n  defaults false" as DRAFT_REQ
  rectangle "Persisted response minimum\n\nRequest fields plus:\n- id\n- href\n- lifecycleStatus = DRAFT\n- isBundle\n  server-resolved" as DRAFT_RESP
  rectangle "May omit until activation\n\n- validFor.startDateTime\n- expressionSpecification\n- expressionSpecification.iri\n- expressionSpecification.expressionLanguage\n- targetEntitySchema\n- specCharacteristic" as DRAFT_OMIT
}

rectangle "Activation gate" as GATE #FFE0B2 {
  rectangle "Validate ACTIVE minimum profile\n\nReject activation if required\nACTIVE fields are missing\n\nPreferred error:\n422 Unprocessable Entity" as VALIDATE
}

rectangle "Minimal ACTIVE profile" as ACTIVE #E0F2F1 {
  rectangle "ACTIVE persisted resource minimum\n\n- id\n- href\n- name\n- version\n- lifecycleStatus = ACTIVE\n- isBundle\n- validFor.startDateTime\n- expressionSpecification\n- expressionSpecification.iri\n- expressionSpecification.expressionLanguage\n- targetEntitySchema\n- specCharacteristic\n- @type\n- @baseType" as ACTIVE_FIELDS
  rectangle "Published runtime contract\n\nUsable for discovery, governance,\nvalidation, and runtime resolution" as ACTIVE_CONTRACT
}

rectangle "Recommended but not\nminimum mandatory" as OPTIONAL #F3E5F5 {
  rectangle "Implementation-specific enrichments\n\n- familyId\n- description\n- relatedParty\n- @schemaLocation\n- validFor.endDateTime\n- schemaVersion / schemaHash\n- _links" as OPTIONAL_FIELDS
}

rectangle "Runtime intent API\nseparate decision" as RUNTIME #ECEFF1 {
  rectangle "Runtime request admission rules\nare owned by the runtime Intent profile\n\nSubmitted runtime admission requires\nboth intentSpecification.id\nand expression.iri.\n\nDraft creation can remain lighter." as RUNTIME_RULE
}

PROFILE --> DRAFT : create as server-managed DRAFT\nedit while DRAFT
DRAFT --> GATE : request activation
GATE --> ACTIVE : full ACTIVE profile satisfied
GATE -[#red,dashed]-> DRAFT : required ACTIVE fields missing
ACTIVE --> RUNTIME : provides active semantic\nand validation contract
PROFILE --> OPTIONAL : may add richer\nimplementation profile fields

note right of DRAFT
Create request does not accept
lifecycleStatus. ID MS sets DRAFT.

If isBundle is omitted,
ID MS defaults it to false.
end note

note right of ACTIVE
expressionSpecification is mandatory
for ACTIVE when expressionSpecification.iri
is mandatory.

targetEntitySchema is the
machine-readable validation contract.

specCharacteristic is the
catalogue / governance view.
end note

note bottom of OPTIONAL
familyId is useful for version-family
governance, but it is not part of the
generic minimum mandatory profile.
end note

note bottom of RUNTIME
This diagram captures the
IntentSpecification profile proposal only.
Runtime Intent mandatory-profile rules
are aligned to the separate runtime proposal:
submitted admission requires both
intentSpecification.id and expression.iri.
end note

@enduml
